		{"id":"bbbb000000000001","type":"text","text":"**Inputs read first**\n- Assignment PDF + HR email (required .md files are graded deliverables)\n- TIER0_REMEDIATION_PLAN.md (8 code fixes, pre-reasoned)\n- CHANGELOG.md (Romanian, pre-git era)\n- design.md (unrelated Qubiz-website research)\n- Empty ASSUMPTIONS/DECISIONS/WHAT_NEXT","x":121,"y":-531,"width":954,"height":362,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"bbbb000000000002","type":"text","text":"**Prior sessions' findings (inherited)**\n- Auth stack genuinely strong (Argon2id, httpOnly+Strict cookies, CSRF, refresh rotation w/ reuse detection)\n- Rate-limit config dead, restore destructive, admin input trusted\n- No real secrets in history; Vault/ gitignore case bug","x":1226,"y":-531,"width":954,"height":362,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"bbbb000000000003","type":"text","text":"**Independent boot check (parallel with debate)**\n- cp .env.example .env\n- docker compose up --build → db+backend+frontend healthy, auto-migrate+seed\n- pytest 28/28, vitest 6/6 baseline","x":2331,"y":-531,"width":854,"height":362,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"bbbb000000000004","type":"text","text":"**Hard constraints**\n- NEVER rewrite history / force-push\n- No `git push` at all (user reviews first)\n- Small incremental commits\n- Vault/ stays untracked","x":3286,"y":-531,"width":854,"height":362,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"cccc000000000001","type":"text","text":"**My draft plan v1**\n- P0: README + 4 docs (verified, honest)\n- P1: TIER0 Items 2, 4+5, 1, 3, 6\n- P2 defer: Item 8 (migration), Item 7 (content)\n- Hygiene: design.md out, EN preface on CHANGELOG\n- Full test + live browser walkthrough","x":121,"y":520,"width":1005,"height":399},
		{"id":"cccc000000000004","type":"text","text":"**Final plan (what changed my mind)**\n- Accepted: docs first; Item 6 promoted; Item 7 cut; Item 8 featured in DECISIONS.md as deliberate risk call; design.md untracked; CHANGELOG preface\n- Partially rejected: kept Items 1 & 3 at the *end* of the queue — verifier's exact line evidence made them low-risk mechanical fixes\n- Order: README → docs → hygiene → Item 2 → 4/5 → 6 → 1 → 3","x":1276,"y":1009,"width":1055,"height":381,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"dddd000000000001","type":"text","text":"**Docs commits**\n- e003847 README (verified run paths)\n- 235cec3 ASSUMPTIONS.md\n- b7297ad DECISIONS.md\n- 9f00b53 WHAT_I_WOULD_DO_NEXT.md\n- 039438b REFLECTION.md\n\nAll grounded in real code + real commit history; warts disclosed (dead rate-limit config, destructive restore, no employee-edit form)","x":121,"y":1643,"width":954,"height":435,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"dddd000000000002","type":"text","text":"**Hygiene commits**\n- 4d1b45d CHANGELOG EN preface + design.md moved to Vault/ (untracked)\n- a28ce15 .gitignore vault/ → Vault/ casing fix (parent session's fix, committed)","x":1176,"y":1643,"width":954,"height":435,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"dddd000000000003","type":"text","text":"**Code commits (TIER0)**\n- 756c6c2 Item 2: server-side pre-boarding gate + tests\n- 50f1e7c Items 4+5: Literal enums + @meridian.com validator (+ latent 422-handler crash fix)\n- ebad532 Item 6: render assigned_desk\n- 8b83d9c Item 1: shared capacity constants, off-by-one fixes\n- aaf4d94 Item 3: restrictedDuringPreboarding prop","x":2231,"y":1643,"width":954,"height":435,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"dddd000000000004","type":"text","text":"**Mid-execution course correction**\n- 3fdb8ca: live testing caught that my role-based gate would lock the seeded demo preboardee out forever (stale role, past hire date)\n- Changed gate to hire_date > today — fixed forward with its own commit, documented in the message","x":3286,"y":1643,"width":854,"height":435,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"dddd000000000005","type":"text","text":"**Explicitly NOT done (and why)**\n- Item 8 real due dates: schema migration 2 days pre-deadline = demo risk; full design published in DECISIONS.md + WHAT_NEXT P1\n- Item 7 guide content: copywriting, no engineering signal → WHAT_NEXT P1/P3\n- Rate-limit middleware, restore audit trail, employee edit form → WHAT_NEXT P2\n- Translating CHANGELOG.md: zero rubric value\n- git push: user's call after review","x":121,"y":2150,"width":2060,"height":399},
		{"id":"dddd000000000006","type":"text","text":"**Process guardrails used per edit**\n- gitnexus impact() before touching each symbol (all LOW/MEDIUM)\n- detect_changes() before each commit (scope matched intent)\n- karpathy-guidelines + solid-grasp-principles loaded before code\n- One logical change per commit, message explains the why","x":2331,"y":2150,"width":1808,"height":399,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"eeee000000000001","type":"text","text":"**Automated suites (final)**\n- pytest: 33 passed (28 baseline + 5 new regression tests)\n- vitest: 6 passed\n- Playwright: 1 passed\n- tsc --noEmit: clean","x":121,"y":2875,"width":954,"height":326,"color":"6"},
